00:34:54.250 --> 00:34:59.420 align:middle line:84%
and it just feels like
a vine of information.

00:34:59.420 --> 00:35:02.180 align:middle line:84%
Like Ian's telling me, he
flashes things on and off

00:35:02.180 --> 00:35:03.680 align:middle line:84%
and he's a little
bit of a jokester,

00:35:03.680 --> 00:35:05.090 align:middle line:84%
so I think you
better be prepared

00:35:05.090 --> 00:35:07.230 align:middle line:84%
because he's going to be
turning things on and off.

00:35:07.230 --> 00:35:08.940 align:middle line:84%
And it might be at
important times.

00:35:08.940 --> 00:35:10.080 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Oh great.

00:35:10.080 --> 00:35:12.080 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAU: I know.

00:35:12.080 --> 00:35:13.290 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: He is a jokester.

00:35:13.290 --> 00:35:15.060 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAU: He knows Tom also.

00:35:15.060 --> 00:35:17.220 align:middle line:90%
He feels very attached to Tom.

00:35:17.220 --> 00:35:18.550 align:middle line:90%
So I do want to say that.

00:35:18.550 --> 00:35:20.360 align:middle line:84%
And he's saying he's
joking around with him

00:35:20.360 --> 00:35:22.170 align:middle line:84%
and he needs him
to pay attention.

00:35:22.170 --> 00:35:24.890 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: He knows Tom and
Tom talked to him a week

00:35:24.890 --> 00:35:26.870 align:middle line:90%
before he died.

00:35:26.870 --> 00:35:29.800 align:middle line:84%
Did not think he
was going to die.

00:35:29.800 --> 00:35:32.990 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAU: Well, sometimes we
don't, you know, and it happens.

00:35:32.990 --> 00:35:36.880 align:middle line:90%
But he's not dead.

00:35:36.880 --> 00:35:38.600 align:middle line:90%
Those are human terms.

00:35:38.600 --> 00:35:39.860 align:middle line:90%
He's more than alive.

00:35:39.860 --> 00:35:43.120 align:middle line:84%
And I think you're more alive
there than you ever are here.

00:35:43.120 --> 00:35:45.380 align:middle line:84%
This is-- this seems
like the dream.

00:35:45.380 --> 00:35:50.450 align:middle line:84%
This seems like the distance
that we here think it is there.

00:35:50.450 --> 00:35:54.365 align:middle line:84%
When you're there,
this is the dream.

00:35:54.365 --> 00:35:56.740 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Tell us about your
book, Infinite Life, Infinite

00:35:56.740 --> 00:35:57.560 align:middle line:90%
Lessons.

00:35:57.560 --> 00:35:58.670 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAU: It's amazing.

00:35:58.670 --> 00:35:59.780 align:middle line:90%
Spirit helped me write it.

00:35:59.780 --> 00:36:01.512 align:middle line:84%
I heard one day you
need to write a book.

00:36:01.512 --> 00:36:02.720 align:middle line:90%
And I said, I'm not a writer.

00:36:02.720 --> 00:36:03.920 align:middle line:84%
And I heard, you
need to write a book.

00:36:03.920 --> 00:36:05.810 align:middle line:84%
You need to stop everything
and write a book.

00:36:05.810 --> 00:36:09.920 align:middle line:84%
And I just sat down and
it came and just flowed.

00:36:09.920 --> 00:36:12.730 align:middle line:84%
It's all about exercises
and integrations.

00:36:12.730 --> 00:36:13.610 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: This is it.

00:36:13.610 --> 00:36:14.410 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAU: Oh, yeah.

00:36:14.410 --> 00:36:15.830 align:middle line:90%
I'm so proud of it.

00:36:15.830 --> 00:36:19.420 align:middle line:10%
And it helps people
understand the spirit world.

00:36:19.420 --> 00:36:20.870 align:middle line:10%
It helps them with dying.

00:36:20.870 --> 00:36:22.730 align:middle line:10%
It helps them with
different kinds of death.

00:36:22.730 --> 00:36:24.460 align:middle line:84%
Like if they have
suicide in their life

00:36:24.460 --> 00:36:27.460 align:middle line:84%
or any of those kinds
of losses, murders.

00:36:27.460 --> 00:36:30.470 align:middle line:84%
It helps people
tap into exercises

00:36:30.470 --> 00:36:32.160 align:middle line:90%
to get closer to spirit.

00:36:32.160 --> 00:36:35.150 align:middle line:84%
It has so much to
offer, and it also

00:36:35.150 --> 00:36:37.650 align:middle line:84%
tells my story of
what happened to me.

00:36:37.650 --> 00:36:40.400 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: There are two ancient
writings, the Egyptian Book

00:36:40.400 --> 00:36:43.820 align:middle line:84%
of the Dead and the Tibetan
Book of the Dead, which

00:36:43.820 --> 00:36:46.730 align:middle line:84%
are training guides for
people, teaching them

00:36:46.730 --> 00:36:49.040 align:middle line:84%
what's the other
side is like, what

00:36:49.040 --> 00:36:51.240 align:middle line:90%
you can expect when you die.

00:36:51.240 --> 00:36:53.440 align:middle line:84%
Is that a little bit
of what yours is?

00:36:53.440 --> 00:36:54.440 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAU: Absolutely.

00:36:54.440 --> 00:36:55.350 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:36:55.350 --> 00:36:59.150 align:middle line:84%
There's so much clarity in it,
and it's easy to understand.

00:36:59.150 --> 00:37:01.820 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Did the spirit kind of
push you into writing this book?

00:37:01.820 --> 00:37:03.230 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAU: 100%.

00:37:03.230 --> 00:37:05.820 align:middle line:84%
I didn't consider
myself a writer.

00:37:05.820 --> 00:37:09.290 align:middle line:84%
I'm writing a second book now
that goes along with this book,

00:37:09.290 --> 00:37:13.010 align:middle line:84%
too, because we have
infinite lessons to learn.

00:37:13.010 --> 00:37:16.700 align:middle line:90%
And so more is coming.

00:37:16.700 --> 00:37:18.810 align:middle line:90%
But it's a really good book.

00:37:18.810 --> 00:37:22.040 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: We had-- a
well-known singer just passed,

00:37:22.040 --> 00:37:23.720 align:middle line:90%
Steve Lawrence.

00:37:23.720 --> 00:37:28.550 align:middle line:84%
His wife, Eydie
Gorm, died in 2013.

00:37:28.550 --> 00:37:33.230 align:middle line:84%
And this is ironic because
a week before he died,

00:37:33.230 --> 00:37:39.990 align:middle line:84%
he was in his '80s, I was online
trying to find out where he was

00:37:39.990 --> 00:37:42.970 align:middle line:90%
to get him on my radio show.

00:37:42.970 --> 00:37:45.370 align:middle line:84%
And we couldn't find
him at that point.

00:37:45.370 --> 00:37:47.750 align:middle line:90%
And then he dies a week later.

00:37:47.750 --> 00:37:50.170 align:middle line:84%
What are the odds
of that happening?

00:37:50.170 --> 00:37:53.710 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAU: Well, it came into
your head for a reason.

00:37:53.710 --> 00:37:54.740 align:middle line:90%
That's how it works.

00:37:54.740 --> 00:37:57.010 align:middle line:84%
The spirit world just
makes things happen

00:37:57.010 --> 00:37:58.940 align:middle line:90%
and they get-- we have notice.

00:37:58.940 --> 00:38:00.110 align:middle line:90%
We're told things.

00:38:00.110 --> 00:38:01.690 align:middle line:90%
We're just not listening.

00:38:01.690 --> 00:38:03.920 align:middle line:90%
We are busy.

00:38:03.920 --> 00:38:06.520 align:middle line:84%
You know, we're doing life
and we're not listening

00:38:06.520 --> 00:38:08.000 align:middle line:90%
to what they're saying to us.

00:38:08.000 --> 00:38:10.730 align:middle line:84%
And they really do want
us to pause and listen.

00:38:10.730 --> 00:38:13.870 align:middle line:84%
And if we stay where
our feet are, literally

00:38:13.870 --> 00:38:16.960 align:middle line:84%
like in this present
moment, if we're present,

00:38:16.960 --> 00:38:19.660 align:middle line:84%
we're able to hear them
and experience them much

00:38:19.660 --> 00:38:21.410 align:middle line:90%
stronger than when we're not.

00:38:21.410 --> 00:38:23.290 align:middle line:84%
And we, on this
planet, walk around

00:38:23.290 --> 00:38:25.160 align:middle line:90%
not present a lot of the time.

00:38:25.160 --> 00:38:27.730 align:middle line:84%
We're working, we're
rushing, we're talking,

00:38:27.730 --> 00:38:30.310 align:middle line:90%
we're, you know, we're busy.

00:38:30.310 --> 00:38:32.540 align:middle line:84%
And so being present
really helps.

00:38:32.540 --> 00:38:35.302 align:middle line:84%
But the odds are very strong
if you're connected to someone

00:38:35.302 --> 00:38:37.510 align:middle line:84%
or you're looking for someone
that they could pop in,

00:38:37.510 --> 00:38:40.460 align:middle line:84%
you just happen to pause
and hear the information.

00:38:40.460 --> 00:38:41.480 align:middle line:90%
His name--

00:38:41.480 --> 00:38:43.180 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: I picked it up.

00:38:43.180 --> 00:38:45.940 align:middle line:84%
What are some of the
common misperceptions

00:38:45.940 --> 00:38:48.190 align:middle line:90%
about life and death?

00:38:48.190 --> 00:38:51.160 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAU: That we are
punished over there

00:38:51.160 --> 00:38:55.338 align:middle line:84%
or that we know-- we have
sins that we have to pay for,

00:38:55.338 --> 00:38:57.380 align:middle line:84%
that we're not going to
see our loved ones, which

00:38:57.380 --> 00:38:59.630 align:middle line:84%
is the furthest
thing from the truth.

00:38:59.630 --> 00:39:00.890 align:middle line:90%
You see them immediately.

00:39:00.890 --> 00:39:03.800 align:middle line:84%
And in hospice, I watch them
see them before they died.

00:39:03.800 --> 00:39:06.720 align:middle line:90%
They were there talking to them.

00:39:06.720 --> 00:39:08.990 align:middle line:90%
We are with them.

00:39:08.990 --> 00:39:12.350 align:middle line:84%
And that they love us
unconditionally no matter what.

00:39:12.350 --> 00:39:14.400 align:middle line:84%
And that your soul
can never be damaged.

00:39:14.400 --> 00:39:18.380 align:middle line:84%
That's a really important
thing, is to recognize that.

00:39:18.380 --> 00:39:19.790 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't get wounds.

00:39:19.790 --> 00:39:22.260 align:middle line:84%
Our spirit does, and spirit
is the breath of life.

00:39:22.260 --> 00:39:24.410 align:middle line:84%
So our spirit, our
heart, our brain, yes,

00:39:24.410 --> 00:39:26.940 align:middle line:84%
gets damaged, but
our soul never.

00:39:26.940 --> 00:39:30.390 align:middle line:84%
It is the only thing we have to
be able to go inward to heal.

00:39:30.390 --> 00:39:33.750 align:middle line:84%
We have to have something in
there or we would never heal.

00:39:33.750 --> 00:39:36.870 align:middle line:84%
And so the soul is there
for us through spirit.

00:39:36.870 --> 00:39:39.110 align:middle line:90%
It always is and always will be.

00:39:39.110 --> 00:39:42.470 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Your book explores
the concept of in-between.

00:39:42.470 --> 00:39:43.940 align:middle line:90%
What is that?

00:39:43.940 --> 00:39:45.780 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAU: It's what
we're doing right now.

00:39:45.780 --> 00:39:48.870 align:middle line:90%
We're not dying in this moment.

00:39:48.870 --> 00:39:50.630 align:middle line:84%
We're not having
the actual crossover

00:39:50.630 --> 00:39:52.410 align:middle line:90%
and we're not being birthed.

00:39:52.410 --> 00:39:54.230 align:middle line:90%
The in-between is life.

00:39:54.230 --> 00:39:55.638 align:middle line:90%
Life on life's terms.

00:39:55.638 --> 00:39:57.180 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Is it good
to be in-between?

00:39:57.180 --> 00:39:58.040 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAU: Absolutely.

00:39:58.040 --> 00:39:59.330 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:39:59.330 --> 00:40:02.810 align:middle line:84%
There's an in-between too,
in between coming back here

00:40:02.810 --> 00:40:04.320 align:middle line:90%
because I was in-between.

00:40:04.320 --> 00:40:05.610 align:middle line:90%
I was in that realm.

00:40:05.610 --> 00:40:07.170 align:middle line:90%
And I felt it and saw it.

00:40:07.170 --> 00:40:09.960 align:middle line:84%
And they spoke to me and told
me I'd be returning to my body.

00:40:09.960 --> 00:40:11.730 align:middle line:90%
And that was in-between also.

00:40:11.730 --> 00:40:13.550 align:middle line:84%
So there's two
separate in-betweens

00:40:13.550 --> 00:40:15.090 align:middle line:90%
and the book talks about that.

00:40:15.090 --> 00:40:16.560 align:middle line:90%
It's like a two-sided mirror.

00:40:16.560 --> 00:40:17.360 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Yeah.

00:40:17.360 --> 00:40:18.000 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAU: Yeah.

00:40:18.000 --> 00:40:19.760 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Do you believe
in reincarnation, Susan?

00:40:19.760 --> 00:40:20.670 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAU: I do.

00:40:20.670 --> 00:40:21.470 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:40:21.470 --> 00:40:23.120 align:middle line:84%
I think it's ego
to think that we

00:40:23.120 --> 00:40:24.750 align:middle line:90%
can do it all in one lifetime.

00:40:24.750 --> 00:40:26.130 align:middle line:90%
There's so much to learn.

00:40:26.130 --> 00:40:28.910 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Do we get better
perceptively each time

00:40:28.910 --> 00:40:29.930 align:middle line:90%
we come back?

00:40:29.930 --> 00:40:30.930 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAU: I believe we do.

00:40:30.930 --> 00:40:33.347 align:middle line:84%
And what's wonderful about
that is that we don't remember.

00:40:33.347 --> 00:40:34.980 align:middle line:84%
And we don't remember
for a reason.

00:40:34.980 --> 00:40:38.130 align:middle line:84%
If I remember it, it
would change my journey.

00:40:38.130 --> 00:40:41.180 align:middle line:84%
I would make different decisions
that my free will wouldn't

00:40:41.180 --> 00:40:42.090 align:middle line:90%
be involved with.

00:40:42.090 --> 00:40:43.770 align:middle line:84%
It would be, oh I
knew that there,

00:40:43.770 --> 00:40:45.530 align:middle line:84%
so I'm not going to do that,
this and that, and this

00:40:45.530 --> 00:40:46.330 align:middle line:90%
and that.

00:40:46.330 --> 00:40:49.340 align:middle line:84%
Instead of allowing myself
to evolve and grow and expand

00:40:49.340 --> 00:40:50.420 align:middle line:90%
in my energy.

00:40:50.420 --> 00:40:52.830 align:middle line:90%
We're here for soul expansion.

00:40:52.830 --> 00:40:55.380 align:middle line:90%
And it's so important for us.

00:40:55.380 --> 00:40:58.820 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Sometimes if you died
in a past life of, let's say,

00:40:58.820 --> 00:41:03.320 align:middle line:84%
a drowning, you're afraid
of water in this life.

00:41:03.320 --> 00:41:04.940 align:middle line:90%
How does that work?

00:41:04.940 --> 00:41:08.210 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAU: Well, I think
it's more a memory,

00:41:08.210 --> 00:41:10.530 align:middle line:90%
an imprint that happens to us.

00:41:10.530 --> 00:41:13.380 align:middle line:90%
And our heart also goes with us.

00:41:13.380 --> 00:41:14.360 align:middle line:90%
Our brain does not.

00:41:14.360 --> 00:41:16.740 align:middle line:84%
Our heart carries
the memories we need.

00:41:16.740 --> 00:41:20.160 align:middle line:84%
And I believe that when we
come back, we have that heart.

00:41:20.160 --> 00:41:23.450 align:middle line:84%
And I'm sure they block out
what we don't-- what we're not

00:41:23.450 --> 00:41:25.620 align:middle line:90%
supposed to on our next round.

00:41:25.620 --> 00:41:28.930 align:middle line:84%
But I think that has
something to do with it.

00:41:28.930 --> 00:41:29.730 align:middle line:90%
I do.

00:41:29.730 --> 00:41:32.340 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I never knew my
grandfather on my father's side.

00:41:32.340 --> 00:41:34.490 align:middle line:90%
He died before I was born.

00:41:34.490 --> 00:41:36.830 align:middle line:90%
He died at about 50.

00:41:36.830 --> 00:41:43.380 align:middle line:84%
But I remember my father as
he got close to that age just

00:41:43.380 --> 00:41:46.380 align:middle line:84%
seemed to panic, you know,
because I think he really

00:41:46.380 --> 00:41:48.340 align:middle line:84%
thought he was
going to go at 50.

00:41:48.340 --> 00:41:51.350 align:middle line:84%
He ended up going
until he was 88.

00:41:51.350 --> 00:41:57.660 align:middle line:84%
But when you look at the
lifestyle of your parents,

00:41:57.660 --> 00:42:00.960 align:middle line:84%
do you sometimes feel
this could happen to me?

00:42:00.960 --> 00:42:02.040 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAU: Absolutely.

00:42:02.040 --> 00:42:04.870 align:middle line:84%
I remember when my father
got pancreatic cancer

00:42:04.870 --> 00:42:08.230 align:middle line:84%
and when he died, I went
to the doctor three times.

00:42:08.230 --> 00:42:11.590 align:middle line:84%
Every time I got an ache or a
pain, I thought, I must have it.

00:42:11.590 --> 00:42:13.890 align:middle line:84%
I think that's our
human condition.

00:42:13.890 --> 00:42:14.980 align:middle line:90%
We have fear.

00:42:14.980 --> 00:42:16.050 align:middle line:90%
And again, like I said--

00:42:16.050 --> 00:42:18.383 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Do you still think
about pancreatic cancer even

00:42:18.383 --> 00:42:19.230 align:middle line:90%
to this day?

00:42:19.230 --> 00:42:19.830 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAU: No, I don't now.

00:42:19.830 --> 00:42:20.705 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Not anymore.

00:42:20.705 --> 00:42:22.240 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAU: But what
we fear, we feed.

00:42:22.240 --> 00:42:24.460 align:middle line:90%
I allow myself to feel it.

00:42:24.460 --> 00:42:26.860 align:middle line:84%
And then I go, no
more fear right now.

00:42:26.860 --> 00:42:28.120 align:middle line:90%
Not today, Susan.

00:42:28.120 --> 00:42:29.037 align:middle line:90%
You don't have it now.

00:42:29.037 --> 00:42:30.412 align:middle line:84%
And if you do,
you don't know it.

00:42:30.412 --> 00:42:31.360 align:middle line:90%
So not today.

00:42:31.360 --> 00:42:32.680 align:middle line:90%
That's what I tell myself.

00:42:32.680 --> 00:42:34.525 align:middle line:84%
And that brings me
back to the now.

00:42:34.525 --> 00:42:35.400 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Eat almonds.

00:42:35.400 --> 00:42:38.350 align:middle line:84%
Edgar Cayce said they
would help fight cancer.

00:42:38.350 --> 00:42:39.480 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAU: Wow.

00:42:39.480 --> 00:42:40.330 align:middle line:90%
I do eat them.

00:42:40.330 --> 00:42:41.050 align:middle line:90%
So that's good.

00:42:41.050 --> 00:42:41.850 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Good.

00:42:41.850 --> 00:42:43.950 align:middle line:90%
Two a day, he said, minimum.

00:42:43.950 --> 00:42:45.250 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAU: That's good to know.

00:42:45.250 --> 00:42:47.400 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: So what's next for you?

00:42:47.400 --> 00:42:50.220 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAU: My second
book, which is actually

00:42:50.220 --> 00:42:52.590 align:middle line:90%
called the Two-Sided Mirror.

00:42:52.590 --> 00:42:56.080 align:middle line:84%
We aren't just souls
having a human experience.

00:42:56.080 --> 00:42:58.340 align:middle line:84%
We are humans having
a soul experience.

00:42:58.340 --> 00:42:59.980 align:middle line:90%
And that's the two sides.

00:42:59.980 --> 00:43:02.550 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You know, the medium
James Van Praagh quite well.

00:43:02.550 --> 00:43:03.350 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAU: I do.

00:43:03.350 --> 00:43:04.730 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: He's one of the best.

00:43:04.730 --> 00:43:06.188 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAU: He's one
of my faves, yeah.

00:43:06.188 --> 00:43:10.250 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: He's very sensitive
and he's had an incredible life.

00:43:10.250 --> 00:43:11.120 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAU: He has.

00:43:11.120 --> 00:43:14.990 align:middle line:84%
I just had dinner with him four
nights ago, five nights ago.

00:43:14.990 --> 00:43:17.440 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What does
James order for dinner?

00:43:17.440 --> 00:43:19.370 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAU: Well, he
got the cookies.

00:43:19.370 --> 00:43:20.777 align:middle line:90%
I definitely he got the cookies.

00:43:20.777 --> 00:43:21.860 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: He loves cookies.

00:43:21.860 --> 00:43:23.132 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAU: Yes, chocolate chip.

00:43:23.132 --> 00:43:25.840 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And he was a consultant
and ghost whisperer, I remember,

00:43:25.840 --> 00:43:26.300 align:middle line:90%
wasn't he?

00:43:26.300 --> 00:43:26.860 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAU: Yes, he was.

00:43:26.860 --> 00:43:27.710 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: A long time ago.

00:43:27.710 --> 00:43:28.580 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAU: He was.

00:43:28.580 --> 00:43:29.840 align:middle line:90%
He's a wonderful man.

00:43:29.840 --> 00:43:30.830 align:middle line:90%
He's very kind.

00:43:30.830 --> 00:43:32.150 align:middle line:90%
He's very helpful.

00:43:32.150 --> 00:43:33.860 align:middle line:90%
He's on your side.

00:43:33.860 --> 00:43:35.540 align:middle line:90%
And I love that.

00:43:35.540 --> 00:43:37.960 align:middle line:84%
That's what I try to be, I
aspire to be that for people.

00:43:37.960 --> 00:43:40.460 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Expert in
reincarnation as well.

00:43:40.460 --> 00:43:41.810 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAU: Yes, he is.

00:43:41.810 --> 00:43:45.720 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What do you tell
someone who's afraid of dying?

00:43:45.720 --> 00:43:51.000 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAU: Well, I think that that
is a normal human condition,

00:43:51.000 --> 00:43:52.210 align:middle line:90%
to be afraid.

00:43:52.210 --> 00:43:53.080 align:middle line:90%
I don't want to die.

00:43:53.080 --> 00:43:54.580 align:middle line:84%
I don't want to
leave my loved ones.

00:43:54.580 --> 00:43:56.440 align:middle line:84%
I'm not afraid of being
on the other side.

00:43:56.440 --> 00:43:58.230 align:middle line:90%
I'm afraid of how I'll die.

00:43:58.230 --> 00:44:01.390 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: There's no rush
to get to the other side.

00:44:01.390 --> 00:44:05.460 align:middle line:84%
But you do think
about it as you age.

00:44:05.460 --> 00:44:08.020 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAU: Yeah, I'm 65
in a couple of months.

00:44:08.020 --> 00:44:09.540 align:middle line:84%
So, yes, I do
think about it as--

00:44:09.540 --> 00:44:11.280 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: I'm 110.

00:44:11.280 --> 00:44:12.300 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:44:12.300 --> 00:44:13.485 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAU: Well, you look
pretty good for 110.

00:44:13.485 --> 00:44:15.750 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Actually, my
mother is going to be 95

00:44:15.750 --> 00:44:19.420 align:middle line:84%
and she's driving herself
and stuff like that.

00:44:19.420 --> 00:44:20.770 align:middle line:90%
She just keeps going.

00:44:20.770 --> 00:44:21.570 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAU: Yeah.

00:44:21.570 --> 00:44:24.240 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: She just keeps going.

00:44:24.240 --> 00:44:26.100 align:middle line:84%
So it's normal and
natural to think

00:44:26.100 --> 00:44:27.660 align:middle line:90%
about the other side, isn't it?

00:44:27.660 --> 00:44:28.460 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAU: It is.

00:44:28.460 --> 00:44:31.950 align:middle line:84%
And it's normal to fear
how you're going to die.

00:44:31.950 --> 00:44:34.553 align:middle line:84%
But if you think of it this
way, if there is no other side,

00:44:34.553 --> 00:44:36.970 align:middle line:84%
you won't know the difference
because there'll be nothing.

00:44:36.970 --> 00:44:38.200 align:middle line:90%
So you won't know.

00:44:38.200 --> 00:44:41.790 align:middle line:84%
So it might be behoove us to
think about the other side

00:44:41.790 --> 00:44:44.560 align:middle line:84%
and think, wow, that
really could be.

00:44:44.560 --> 00:44:46.250 align:middle line:90%
And wouldn't that be exciting?

00:44:46.250 --> 00:44:47.560 align:middle line:90%
Why not?

00:44:47.560 --> 00:44:49.090 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't harm us.

00:44:49.090 --> 00:44:52.720 align:middle line:84%
So if you do fear death,
usually our humanness

00:44:52.720 --> 00:44:55.420 align:middle line:84%
fears how we're
going to die, not

00:44:55.420 --> 00:44:56.840 align:middle line:90%
being on the other side or not.

00:44:56.840 --> 00:44:59.050 align:middle line:84%
Because there's nothing
to fear if it isn't there.

00:44:59.050 --> 00:45:02.480 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Do we get to pick
our reincarnated next life?

00:45:02.480 --> 00:45:03.280 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAU: Yes.

00:45:03.280 --> 00:45:05.650 align:middle line:84%
There's a room called
the room of knowledge.

00:45:05.650 --> 00:45:07.192 align:middle line:84%
A lot of people call
it the Akashic--

00:45:07.192 --> 00:45:07.992 align:middle line:90%
I don't even--

00:45:07.992 --> 00:45:09.260 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: The Akashic Records.

00:45:09.260 --> 00:45:10.060 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAU: Thank you.

00:45:10.060 --> 00:45:11.860 align:middle line:84%
I don't even-- it's
so out of my box

00:45:11.860 --> 00:45:14.360 align:middle line:84%
because they taught me it
was the room of knowledge.

00:45:14.360 --> 00:45:16.040 align:middle line:10%
And that's what I call it.

00:45:16.040 --> 00:45:19.490 align:middle line:10%
And in there, I saw them
making choices and decisions.

00:45:19.490 --> 00:45:21.730 align:middle line:84%
And I actually saw them
discouraging some of it,

00:45:21.730 --> 00:45:23.990 align:middle line:84%
like you don't want to
go through all that.

00:45:23.990 --> 00:45:27.170 align:middle line:90%
And we have free will.

00:45:27.170 --> 00:45:29.420 align:middle line:84%
And so I heard them
say, yes, I do.

00:45:29.420 --> 00:45:31.270 align:middle line:90%
I can handle it.

00:45:31.270 --> 00:45:33.770 align:middle line:84%
But, you know, free will
is involved in everything.

00:45:33.770 --> 00:45:35.608 align:middle line:90%
Everything is not planned.

00:45:35.608 --> 00:45:36.650 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That is so true.

00:45:36.650 --> 00:45:38.860 align:middle line:84%
How do people get a
hold of you, Susan?

00:45:38.860 --> 00:45:42.170 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAU: They can go
to ssusangrau.com.

00:45:42.170 --> 00:45:45.730 align:middle line:10%
They can go to social
media, Susan Grau Official.

00:45:45.730 --> 00:45:48.290 align:middle line:10%
They can call my lines.

00:45:48.290 --> 00:45:50.140 align:middle line:84%
They go online and
just type in Susan Grau

00:45:50.140 --> 00:45:51.832 align:middle line:90%
and they'll see it populate.

00:45:51.832 --> 00:45:53.540 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Thanks for
being on the program.

00:45:53.540 --> 00:45:54.320 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAU: Thanks for having me.

00:45:54.320 --> 00:45:55.043 align:middle line:90%
I had a really good time.

00:45:55.043 --> 00:45:55.310 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

00:45:55.310 --> 00:45:55.940 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Me too.

00:45:55.940 --> 00:45:56.740 align:middle line:90%
Me too.

00:45:56.740 --> 00:45:59.410 align:middle line:84%
There was a time, I'll
be honest with you,

00:45:59.410 --> 00:46:02.770 align:middle line:84%
I doubted the existence
of the other side.

00:46:02.770 --> 00:46:06.040 align:middle line:84%
I had a friend of mine who
died in a motorcycle accident

00:46:06.040 --> 00:46:08.080 align:middle line:90%
and I went to his funeral.

00:46:08.080 --> 00:46:12.130 align:middle line:84%
And I'm looking at
the body, and it just

00:46:12.130 --> 00:46:14.210 align:middle line:90%
dawned on me that it was over.

00:46:14.210 --> 00:46:15.680 align:middle line:90%
It was done for him.

00:46:15.680 --> 00:46:19.990 align:middle line:84%
But then all of a sudden, I had
this stark feeling of loneliness

00:46:19.990 --> 00:46:22.900 align:middle line:90%
that wore off instantly.

00:46:22.900 --> 00:46:28.030 align:middle line:84%
And I felt happy again because
I know he lives forever.

00:46:28.030 --> 00:46:30.640 align:middle line:84%
Thanks for watching
Beyond Belief.

